segment.source: Load Symbols or Configure Symbol Paths
segment.target: Load Symbols or Configure Symbol Paths

segment.source: In Windows Performance Analyzer (WPA), you can set a recording to load symbols or change symbol paths.
segment.target: In Windows Performance Analyzer (WPA), you can set a recording to load symbols or change symbol paths.

segment.source: To set a recording to load symbols
segment.target: To set a recording to load symbols

segment.source: On the Trace menu, click Load Symbols.
segment.target: On the Trace menu, click Load Symbols.

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: When you click Load Symbols, a progress bar (along with a count of the symbols found) above the Graph Explorer windows and the Analysis tab.
segment.target: When you click Load Symbols, a progress bar (along with a count of the symbols found) above the Graph Explorer windows and the Analysis tab.

segment.source: In addition, on the graph itself, the data areas become grayed-out and a progress bar displays in each data area.
segment.target: In addition, on the graph itself, the data areas become grayed-out and a progress bar displays in each data area.

segment.source: To change symbol paths
segment.target: To change symbol paths

segment.source: On the Trace menu, click Configure Symbol Paths.
segment.target: On the Trace menu, click Configure Symbol Paths.

segment.source: By default, the dialog opens on the Paths tab
segment.target: By default, the dialog opens on the Paths tab

segment.source: Enter or select the desired paths, and then click OK.
segment.target: Enter or select the desired paths, and then click OK.

segment.source: To cache symbol files to a SymCache folder
segment.target: To cache symbol files to a SymCache folder

segment.source: On the Trace menu, click Configure Symbol Paths.
segment.target: On the Trace menu, click Configure Symbol Paths.

segment.source: By default, the dialog opens on the Paths tab.
segment.target: By default, the dialog opens on the Paths tab.

segment.source: Click SymCache.
segment.target: Click SymCache.

segment.source: All stored files (with their corresponding paths) display in the body of the SymCache tab, which you can scroll to find specific SymCache file paths.
segment.target: All stored files (with their corresponding paths) display in the body of the SymCache tab, which you can scroll to find specific SymCache file paths.

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: Invalid paths display in red.
segment.target: Invalid paths display in red.

segment.source: Select SymCache generation folder and then click the Browse for Folder icon to search for the location where your SymCache files are stored, and then click OK on the Browse for Folder dialog.
segment.target: Select SymCache generation folder and then click the Browse for Folder icon to search for the location where your SymCache files are stored, and then click OK on the Browse for Folder dialog.

segment.source: Select each SymCache path to save to the SymCache generation folder specified in the previous steps, and then click OK.
segment.target: Select each SymCache path to save to the SymCache generation folder specified in the previous steps, and then click OK.

segment.source: To change load settings when configuring symbols
segment.target: To change load settings when configuring symbols

segment.source: On the Trace menu, click Configure Symbol Paths.
segment.target: On the Trace menu, click Configure Symbol Paths.

segment.source: By default, the dialog opens on the Paths tab.
segment.target: By default, the dialog opens on the Paths tab.

segment.source: Click Load Settings.
segment.target: Click Load Settings.

segment.source: Select how you want to load symbols based on the following options:
segment.target: Select how you want to load symbols based on the following options:

segment.source: Load symbols after load
segment.target: Load symbols after load

segment.source: Load symbols per the following restrictions:
segment.target: Load symbols per the following restrictions:

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: When selecting the Load symbols per the following restrictions: option, you can specify whether you want to load symbols for specifi processes or you can choose to not load symbols for specific images.
segment.target: When selecting the Load symbols per the following restrictions: option, you can specify whether you want to load symbols for specifi processes or you can choose to not load symbols for specific images.

segment.source: You can opt to specify restrictions for both processes and images.
segment.target: You can opt to specify restrictions for both processes and images.

segment.source: Click OK.
segment.target: Click OK.
